# Lets Talk
The {project_name:} community is here to help you

--- name:content
We really want you to get involved in the {project_name:} and we love [contributions](contributing.html). One of the easiest ways to get involved is to join the community discussions.

# Mailing List

The main mailing list is hosted at the [scalate google group](http://groups.google.com/group/scalate).

 * [http://groups.google.com/group/scalate](http://groups.google.com/group/scalate)

Please join us! 

Be aware that to reduce spam your first post will be moderated through; so please be patient. (Unfortunately we get a lot of spam)

### Commits Mailing List

The [scalate-commits google group](http://groups.google.com/group/scalate-commits) is notified of all changes to the source code or changes to [issues](support.html) so you can use this list to watch development and support occur.

* [http://groups.google.com/group/scalate-commits](http://groups.google.com/group/scalate-commits)

### Old Archives

Previously to moving to the [google group](http://groups.google.com/group/scalate), we hosted scalate mailing lists on Nabble here:

* [scalate-dev](http://n3.nabble.com/scalate-f143585.html)
* [scalate-commits](http://n3.nabble.com/scalate-commits-f143594.html)

# Twitter

You can watch us on twitter by following [@scalate](http://twitter.com/scalate) or alternatively searching for [scalate](http://search.twitter.com/search?q=scalate) or the [#scalate](http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23scalate) tag.

If you find something you like or don't like in scalate please do tweet it (with scalate or #scalate in the text) or lets chat about it on the [mailing list](http://groups.google.com/group/scalate)

# IRC

You can also catch us on IRC to chat via **#scalate** on **irc.freenode.net**
